title: Tally of Republican votes in the primary, Michigan, 2008
name: Tally of Republican votes in the primary, Michigan, 2008
description: These maps are based on the Michigan Secretary of State Election Website (1) as of 10 minutes past Midnight, January 16, 2008. These are uncertified" results. This is Romney's first win and probably saved him from dropping out of the primaries after finishing 2nd both in Iowa and New Hampshire. McCain and Huckabee finished 2nd and 3rd respectively. With Romney's win in Michigan the GOP has no clear cut front runner.  Romney got nearly 38.9% votes (~337550) to McCain's 29.7% (257400) followed by Huckabee at 16% (~139600).
